The article argues against politicizing national security interests and emphasizes the importance of meeting core national security needs without demanding offsets. It mentions the support for Israel and defense of Ukraine as bipartisan priorities, highlighting the humanitarian aid needed in Gaza and the need to help Ukraine defend its sovereignty against Russian forces. The article also mentions bipartisan support for investing in border security and criticizes using national security as leverage for other political agendas. It warns against threatening the funding for Israel's self-defense and calls for maintaining the commitment to one of the United States' closest allies.